'''Bally Glacier''' ({{Coord|81|22|S|159|12|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] {{convert|6|nmi|km}} long which occupies the central part of the [[Carlstrom Foothills]] of the [[Churchill Mountains]]. It flows north along the east side of [[Mount Blick]] into [[Jorda Glacier]]. It was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] after [[John Bally]] of the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]] Center for Astrophysics and Space Astronomy, [[Boulder, CO]]; he was a [[United States Antarctic Program]] principal investigator and field team member of the Advanced Telescope Project, [[Amundsen–Scott South Pole Station|South Pole]] Center for Astrophysical Research in Antarctica, 1992–95.<ref name=gnis/>
