'''Cilix''' is a small [[Impact crater|crater]] on [[Europa (moon)|Europa]] that serves as the reference point for the moon's system of [[longitude]]. The longitude of Cilix's center is defined as being 182° W, thus establishing the moon's [[prime meridian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/1216|title=Planetary Names: Crater, craters: Cilix on Europa|website=planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov}}</ref>
Cilix is about 15&nbsp;km in diameter.
