'''Elizabeth Rosa Landau''' is an American journalist and science communicator. She is the Senior Storyteller at the NASA [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]].
== Education == Landau grew up in [[Bryn Mawr, Pennsylvania]], where she watched [[Carl Sagan]]'s TV series [[Cosmos (television series)|Cosmos.]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://solarsystem.nasa.gov/people/4158/elizabeth-landau/|title=Solar System Exploration: NASA Science|website=Solar System Exploration: NASA Science|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref>
Landau earned a bachelor's degree in anthropology at [[Princeton University]] ([[Latin honors|magna cum laude]]) in 2006. As a student, she completed study-abroad programs at [[University of Seville]] and [[Universidad de León]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.princeton.edu/oip/announcements/archive/index.xml?id=16304|title=ARCHIVE&nbsp;-&nbsp;Office of International Programs|last=University|first=Princeton|website=www.princeton.edu|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref> On her return, she became a production intern at [[CNN en Español]] in New York.<ref name=":1" /> She earned a master’s in journalism from [[Columbia University]], where she focused on politics.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bestpitchievergot.com/elizabeth-landau/|title=Using Images To Pitch Your Story To Journalists - NASA & Former CNN Writer Elizabeth Landau|date=2015-04-01|work=Best Pitch I Ever Got|access-date=2018-03-10|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Career == Landau began to write and produce for [[CNN]] in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://muckrack.com/lizlandau/bio|title=Elizabeth Landau’s Biography {{!}} Muck Rack|website=muckrack.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref> Here she co-founded the [[CNN]] science blog, Light Years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lightyears.blogs.cnn.com/|title=Light Years|website=lightyears.blogs.cnn.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref> She covered a variety of topics including [[Pi Day]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2014/03/14/tech/innovation/pi-day-math-celebrations/index.html|title=Pi Day 2014 celebrated throughout the United States - CNN|last=CNN|first=By Elizabeth Landau,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2013/03/14/health/pi-day-memorizing-numbers/index.html|title=On Pi Day, finding strength in numbers - CNN|last=CNN|first=By Elizabeth Landau,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/TECH/03/12/pi.day.math/index.html|title=On Pi Day, one number 'reeks of mystery' - CNN.com|last=CNN|first=By Elizabeth Landau,|access-date=2018-06-11|language=en}}</ref> In 2012 Landau interviewed [[Scott Maxwell (engineer)|Scott Maxwell]] about the [[Curiosity (rover)|Curiosity]] rover, which was her first visit to the NASA [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2012/08/04/us/mars-rover-scott-maxwell/|title=His other car is on Mars - CNN|last=CNN|first=By Elizabeth Landau,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-03-10}}</ref> In 2014 she became media specialist at the NASA [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]], where she led media strategy for [[Dawn (spacecraft)]], [[Voyager program|Voyager]], [[Spitzer Space Telescope|Spitzer]], [[NuSTAR]], [[Wide-field Infrared Survey Explorer|WISE]], [[Planck (spacecraft)|Planck]] and [[Herschel Space Observatory|Hershel]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/m/news/news.php?feature=4508#.WqQ94pPFLy8|title=Jet Propulsion