{{Speciesbox | name = Setzer's mouse-tailed dormouse | image = | status = DD | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{Cite journal | author = Kryštufek, B. | author2 = Amori, G. | author3 = Mitsain, G. | last-author-amp = yes | title = ''Myomimus setzeri'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 2008 | page = e.T14089A4389600 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 2008 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/14089/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2008.RLTS.T14089A4389600.en | access-date = 13 December 2017}}</ref> | genus = Myomimus | species = setzeri | authority = Rossolimo, 1976 | synonyms = }}
The '''Setzer's mouse-tailed dormouse''' (''Myomimus setzeri'') is a species of [[rodent]] in the family [[Gliridae]]. It is [[endemic]] to [[Iran]]. Very little amounts of information is known about this [[Myomimus]] Family Member, with just only 10 specimens known. It is found mainly in the pellets of the [[Eurasian eagle owl]].<ref name=Aulagnier>Aulagnier S.; P. Haffner, A. J. Mitchell-Jones, F. Moutou & J. Zima (2009) ''Mammals of Europe, North Africa and the Middle East'', A&C Black, London.</ref>
